TARGET: control module signal reference wiring (internal common ground points),
DESCRIPTION: Test for the presence and integrity of all internal ground/common reference connections within the control module, particularly between subcircuits (sensor, relay, potentiometers, opamp/comparator). Probe for broken or missing internal links that do not appear in initial rail/ground tests but may cause floating references or inadvertent feedback.,
RESULT: All tested subcircuits (relay, potentiometers, sensor bias resistor) share a common node (net_5), confirming intact ground/common reference connections among them. The ambient light sensor connects to these points through a resistive path (~5000 Ω), and there are no open or floating references detected between these units. No polarity inversions were observed in these probe results.
