description: Measure the voltage output from the ambient light sensor under steady light conditions to determine if the light sensor is producing an unstable or oscillating signal that could cause the relay to switch. Verify if the output is steady or fluctuating abnormally, suggesting a fault in the light sensor or its immediate circuitry., outcome='The voltage measured at the ambient light sensor shows 5.94 V (positive terminal) and 0.02 V (negative terminal), but the simulation did not converge, indicating that the circuit is in an unstable or oscillating state. This suggests the light sensor output is not steady under tested conditions.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=25.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> control module power rails / reference connections,
description: Test for proper voltage and continuity between the power supply rails and reference (ground) in the control module. Verify that all ground and supply connections are correctly referenced and not floating, as a missing ground or floating supply in the control module could cause instability or oscillatory behavior., outcome='All power and ground cables show nominal continuity (0.1 Ω) and correct voltage levels relative to ground. No floating or missing supply rails detected. However, the simulation did not converge, indicating circuit instability or oscillatory behavior despite correct rail and ground referencing.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=160.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> control module signal reference wiring (internal common ground points),
description: Test for the presence and integrity of all internal ground/common reference connections within the control module, particularly between subcircuits (sensor, relay, potentiometers, opamp/comparator). Probe for broken or missing internal links that do not appear in initial rail/ground tests but may cause floating references or inadvertent feedback., outcome='All tested subcircuits (relay, potentiometers, sensor bias resistor) share a common node (net_5), confirming intact ground/common reference connections among them. The ambient light sensor connects to these points through a resistive path (~5000 Ω), and there are no open or floating references detected between these units. No polarity inversions were observed in these probe results.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=315.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> control module comparator/op-amp circuit,
description: Test the output of the comparator or operational amplifier in the control module under steady input conditions to verify if it is oscillating or unstable. Measure the output pin with an oscilloscope or voltmeter, and check for expected steady or threshold-crossing behavior. This can help determine if the instability is being generated at the amplification or threshold-detection stage., outcome="The circuit is in an unstable or oscillating state, as indicated by the simulation not converging during voltage measurements at the 'Ambient Light Sensor'. All voltage readings were successfully taken, and no polarity inversions were detected in the cable connections.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.", precise_action_cost=205.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> control module comparator/op-amp negative feedback network,
description: Test the integrity of the negative feedback path of the comparator/op-amp in the control module. Check for open circuits, missing feedback resistor, or miswiring that would prevent proper feedback and could cause oscillation or instability., outcome="The sensor bias resistor has nominal continuity (measured resistance matches the nominal value of 10,000 Ω). Simulation did not converge, indicating the circuit is currently unstable or oscillating. No polarity inversion or open circuit detected at the 'Sensor Bias Resistor' measurement point.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.", precise_action_cost=25.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
