name: Test -> control module relay contacts (mechanical continuity and state),
description: Test the mechanical continuity and switching state of the relay contacts in the control module using a continuity meter. This will confirm that the relay is cleanly opening and closing on command, and does not have stuck or bouncing contacts that may cause oscillation or instability., outcome='The inspection panel was successfully opened, and the resistance measurement across the control relay shows nominal continuity (0.01 Ω as expected). However, the simulation reports that the circuit is in an unstable or oscillating state, despite proper contact closure.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=25.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> control module circuit board (check for missing timing/decoupling components),
description: Test for the physical presence (by continuity/resistance testing) of the timing and/or decoupling capacitors that may be essential for stable operation of the comparator/op-amp circuit. Often a missing or failed capacitor (open circuit) can cause instability or oscillation, even if not visually obvious. Probe across where the timing or decoupling capacitor should be, and confirm continuity or presence., outcome='The requested action could not be mapped to any recognized diagnostic operation. Only actions from the available action list are supported (e.g. measure_voltage, test_continuity, inspect_connections, verify_repair, …).\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=0.0, cost_breakdown=[], simplified_outcome=None)] 
